{
  "stem": "10862.3",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But some of them were very kind, and they would give us bread.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And some of them were not so kind.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Some of them would yell at us, dirty Jew, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Dirty Jew, get out.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And some of them were kind.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Some of them were kind.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, I remember once coming into a Polish home where they were giving us food, and they would give us shelter.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they told us we could bathe, and it was-- they were very, very warm.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But one day this was still going on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Going back, as we were leaving the camp-- I left this out.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "As we were leaving the camp, the Russians were still bombing the city because, you know, when you were liberated you became like an animal and the gates were open and you just ran in different directions.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Well, the three-- my sister Anne and my sister Eda and I stuck together, and as we were walking out of the camp, the Russians were still bombing the camps and they were bombing the city.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And a bomb fell right in front of us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "One guy was killed, another girl was wounded, terribly wounded.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "My sister was wounded on her head, but it was a flesh wound, but blood was starting coming out of-- and we could see the blood in the snow.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And we didn't know-- we thought for sure she has really been hit badly, but fortunately for her, it was just a scratch type.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "It wasn't a deep cut.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But it was bad enough where blood was coming out and would see the blood in the snow.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We finally were able-- and my sister Eda, as she was hearing the bombs-- a bomb makes a certain sound when it's ready to fall.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
